Anonymous Fri 30 Aug 2024 21:31:37 No.68730630 Report
Quoted By: >>68731047
>>68730259
Large capacity hard drives are piss cheap nowadays. Just look for something that uses CMR and get a 3.5" external bay and boom, you got a ghetto backup. You can then sync your shit using FreeFIleSync and now you have two local copies of your data, basic media redundancy. and technically speaking a 3-2-1 backup

As for the folder size, ~6GB is nothing nowadays. Unless you're badly limited by upload speeds that is. You could put that into a .7z file and drop it on some file sharing site. If it has a size limit you could split the archive, but then you have to be aware of the order when the file host renames them so that they can be renamed again so that the unpacker knows the right order. I could go on about potential ways to share large shit anonymously since computers are my forte and this topic is something I've looked into a lot.
